### OVERVIEW  
The study identifies widespread faint black hole activity in nearby galaxies, solidified by advanced radio measurements.  

### KEY HIGHLIGHTS  
- Detected in nearly one-quarter of observed galaxies;  
- Analyzed 280 nearby galaxies using high-resolution surveys;  
- Confirms presence of weakly active supermassive black holes;  
- Reveals jet-like structures and enhanced accretion activity;  
- Validated findings through complementary X-ray data;  

### ARTICLE  
The analysis highlights significant contributions to understanding galactic black hole dynamics through high-resolution observations.
